1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3787 By: Sneed
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to elections; prohibiting persons who
are not a natural-born citizen of the United States
8 from holding elected office; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
9
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-113 of Title 26, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 No person who is not a natural-born citizen of the United States
17 may hold elected municipal, county, state, or other government
18 office in the State of Oklahoma.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
